Pre-Game Insights: The Phoenix Suns will face the Utah Jazz at the Footprint Center on January 11, 2025. Both teams have been underperforming this season, with the Suns ranked 12th and the Jazz 14th in the West.
Key players include Devin Booker and Kevin Durant for the Suns, and Collin Sexton and Lauri Markkanen for the Jazz.

The last game between the Jazz and the Suns took place on December 13, 2024. The Suns won that game with an eight-point margin. This upcoming match will be the third meeting of this season between the Suns and the Jazz. So far, the Suns have won both of their games against Utah.

The Suns have too much quality on their roster to drop a game to a team as weak as the Utah Jazz. They’ve won both of their games against Utah this season and it wouldn’t surprise anyone if the Suns end up sweeping the season series. We predict that the Suns will win this game in dominant fashion.
Our Prediction: The Suns will win.
